steps.content:
Rearrange the equation to isolate $\cos 2x$:

$$
\begin{aligned} 
2a\cos 2x &= -b \\ 
\cos 2x &= -\frac{b}{2a} 
\end{aligned}
$$

Now we rearrange to solve for $\cos^2 x$:

$$
\begin{aligned} 
2\cos^2 x &= \frac{3}{4} + 1 \\ 
2\cos^2 x &= \frac{7}{4} \\ 
\cos^2 x &= \frac{7}{8} 
\end{aligned}
$$

Now we solve the remaining equation for $\cos^2 x$:

$$
\begin{aligned} 
4(2\cos^2 x - 1) - 3 &= 0 \\ 
8\cos^2 x - 4 - 3 &= 0 \\ 
8\cos^2 x - 7 &= 0 \\ 
8\cos^2 x &= 7 \\ 
\cos^2 x &= \frac{7}{8} 
\end{aligned}
$$
